{"mem_mp9b6z5n_d4ab2991cb78":{"concepts":["funnel","diagnosis","triage","A/B/C","version-extraction","lab.db","CLAUDE.md ┬¦8"],"content":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦8 A/B/C triage for \"tech detected, version absent, rules exist\" bugs. Three root causes, identified BEFORE writing any code: (A) rule wrong/incomplete - fix by lab.db row INSERT, no code change. (B) right content never reached the rule - data plumbing fix at the stage boundary, on the CONSUMER side. (C) no funnel stage covers this content source - add a new uniform stage driven by lab.db rules. Triage test: if you can write the matching lab.db row, it's A. If an existing rule would match but the content isn't reaching it, it's B. If neither, it's C. Validated 2026-05-17 on careforvietnam.vn font-awesome bug: rule existed (Cause A ruled out), URL was relative so curl_cffi rejected the fetch (Cause B). Fix went into BodyExtractStage._candidate_asset_urls (consumer side, urljoin against page URL), NOT into scanner._find_matcher_evidence_url. After fix: font-awesome version=4.7.0 emerged.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:45.370Z","files":["D:\\DATN2\\CLAUDE.md","D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\stages.py","D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\scanner.py"],"id":"mem_mp9b6z5n_d4ab2991cb78","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦8 A/B/C triage for \"tech detected, version absent, rules exist\" bugs.","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:45.370Z","version":1},"mem_mp9b74zg_4d038824081f":{"concepts":["producer","consumer","plumbing","scanner","stages","raw-signal","boundary"],"content":"When a stage can't consume what a prior stage produced, the fix goes on the CONSUMER side. The producer (scanner, raw extractors) stays a faithful echo of the raw signal. Don't add convenience normalisation to widely-consumed producer modules - different consumers may need different normalisation, and debugging wants the raw form. Specifically: scanner._find_matcher_evidence_url returns raw href values; stages that fetch (BodyExtractStage) resolve relative URLs themselves via urljoin against the detection's page URL. User explicitly rejected producer-side urljoin fix during 2026-05-17 session with \"you are hardcoding again. i want rules\" - even though urljoin is RFC 3986 plumbing not a rule.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:52.923Z","files":["D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\scanner.py","D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\stages.py"],"id":"mem_mp9b74zg_4d038824081f","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"When a stage can't consume what a prior stage produced, the fix goes on the CONS","type":"preference","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:52.923Z","version":1},"mem_mp9b76q3_4e7f4b04654c":{"concepts":["CloakBrowser","Playwright","chromium","binary","download","junction","env-override","VN-network"],"content":"CloakBrowser stealth Chromium download from cloakbrowser.dev (Azure Blob) is throttled to ~110 KB/s from VN - 562 MB binary takes ~85min and frequently aborts mid-download leaving zombie tmp*.zip files in %TEMP%. Workaround: directory junction (no admin needed on Windows) from CloakBrowser's expected path to existing Playwright chromium. Command: `mklink /J C:\\Users\\hungc\\.cloakbrowser\\chromium-146.0.7680.177.4 C:\\Users\\hungc\\AppData\\Local\\ms-playwright\\chromium-1217\\chrome-win64`. After junction, binary_info() returns installed=True with no env var needed. Verified: cloak page mode produces real Chrome JA4 with h2 indicator and Akamai HTTP/2 hash 52d84b11... identical to curl_cffi chrome120. Cloak api mode (APIRequestContext) is HTTP/1.1 only - worse fingerprint than curl_cffi for unblocked targets. Stage 5 escalation uses mode=\"page\" automatically when cdn_block detected.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:55.178Z","files":["D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\cloak_fetcher.py","D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\cli.py"],"id":"mem_mp9b76q3_4e7f4b04654c","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"CloakBrowser stealth Chromium download from cloakbrowser.dev (Azure Blob) is thr","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:55.178Z","version":1},"mem_mp9b78d7_af0ce8b98c9a":{"concepts":["whatweb","empty-db","0-hits","importer","cause-A"],"content":"WhatWeb stage always logs \"+0 hits\" because whatweb.db has only 3 technologies / 3 patterns - WhatWeb upstream has ~1800 plugins. ww_stats shows imported_techs=0 even though 3 rows exist - the importer never finished a clean run (or rows are partial/test seed). Cause A per CLAUDE.md ┬¦8: rule data is missing. Fix when ready: `python -m fp.cli whatweb-import --db whatweb.db`. No code change needed - plumbing is intact (Scanner.ww_cache loaded, scan_response called on root_resp, _stage(\"whatweb begin\") prints, just returns empty list because regex base is tiny).","createdAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:57.306Z","files":["D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\whatweb.db","D:\\DATN2\\fingerprinter\\fp\\whatweb.py"],"id":"mem_mp9b78d7_af0ce8b98c9a","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"WhatWeb stage always logs \"+0 hits\" because whatweb.db has only 3 technologies /","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T05:02:57.306Z","version":1},"mem_mp9oxaae_0a162e84cadc":{"concepts":["lab-cycle","source-grounded","no-fabricated-citation","claude-md-section-10"],"content":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 (added 2026-05-17): \"No Fabricated Citations -- The Source claim must be earned.\" A rule's note/source_json field is a load-bearing provenance claim. Writing \"Source: <docs URL>\" without fetching that URL in the same turn is citation-shaped text that hides a ┬¦6 violation from later review. Mandatory lab cycle order: (1) Fetch official docs; (2) Download representative samples across documented variants the corpus does NOT contain; (3) Inspect bodies; (4) Write rule with specific citations; (5) Validate against corpus separately, last. Worked example from this session: jsdelivr /npm/ rule. Initial pass grep'd 7 corpus URLs, wrote regex that fit, fabricated \"Source: jsdelivr.com/docs\" citation. User pushed back. Actually fetching docs revealed @MAJOR / @MAJOR.MINOR range aliases the corpus didn't contain; downloading proved @5/... serves Bootstrap 5.3.8 body. 3-part-required regex was correct by accident; fabricated citation would have shielded that gap from audit. For \"find rules for X\" tasks, FIRST tool call is WebFetch on official docs, NOT Grep over scan_results.jsonl. Grep-first is ┬¦6 in operational disguise.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:07.860Z","files":["D:/DATN2/CLAUDE.md","D:/DATN2/lab/research/jsdelivr/README.md","C:/Users/hungc/.claude/projects/D--DATN2/memory/feedback_no_fabricated_citations.md"],"id":"mem_mp9oxaae_0a162e84cadc","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 (added 2026-05-17): \"No Fabricated Citations -- The Source claim m","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:07.860Z","version":1},"mem_mp9oxwnz_472b2f1a0599":{"concepts":["backtest","denominator-discipline","per-slice","dashboard-count","live-refetch","claude-md-section-11"],"content":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦11 (added 2026-05-17): \"Backtest Against The Right Slice -- Denominator Discipline.\" A rule's coverage % is meaningless without the correct denominator. Three failure modes in order of subtlety: (1) No filter, run against full corpus -> \"4/32146\" buries misses in catalog noise; (2) Filter by archived evidence URLs in scan_results.jsonl -> \"5/7 = 71%\" inflated because scan archives are SUMMARIES, not the page reference graph; (3) CORRECT: use the dashboard's \"tech never versioned\" count as denominator (37 targets for jsdelivr), then LIVE re-fetch each target's HTML and extract every CDN reference -- finds ~40 URLs (30 invisible in archived JSON), rule covers 15/40 = ~37% URL coverage, 14/37 = 38% target lift. Miss surface dominated by 16 alias-table gaps (dayjs, gsap, slick-carousel, select2, @mdi/font, etc.) NOT regex gaps -- pointing to lab_pkg_aliases INSERTs as the follow-up, not regex widening. Miss classification mandatory: every miss gets a label (rule-side / data-side / plumbing / out-of-scope / intentionally-rejected). Without labels, a miss count is unactionable. The denominator must match the metric the consumer (dashboard) reports. For CDN-shape and body-channel rules: scan archives are not the reference graph, live-fetch is required.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:36.861Z","files":["D:/DATN2/CLAUDE.md","D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/dashboard/analyzer.py","D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/_jsd_proper_backtest.py","C:/Users/hungc/.claude/projects/D--DATN2/memory/feedback_per_slice_backtest.md"],"id":"mem_mp9oxwnz_472b2f1a0599","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"CLAUDE.md ┬¦11 (added 2026-05-17): \"Backtest Against The Right Slice -- Denominat","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:36.861Z","version":1},"mem_mp9oxxq8_e7e58ba0d8a5":{"concepts":["wappalyzer","evidence-url","scripsrc","scanner","plumbing-fix","slick-cello.vn"],"content":"Wappalyzer evidence_url propagation (fixed 2026-05-17). Producer-side plumbing fix per CLAUDE.md ┬¦8 cause B. Before: when Wappalyzer's scriptSrc/scripts matcher fired, _match_pattern returned only the re.Match -- discarded which script URL triggered it; _wap_to_detection in scanner.py did not propagate evidence_url even if available. Result: all Wappalyzer-detected techs with scriptSrc matchers (Slick on cello.vn was the worked example) emitted evidence_url=null. Downstream BodyExtractStage had no asset URL to fetch for banner-rule version rescue. Fix: (1) _match_pattern now returns (match, matched_script_src) tuple; first scriptSrc/scripts hit's URL is recorded; (2) evaluate() carries evidence_url through to the detection dict; (3) scanner._wap_to_detection propagates evidence_url to the Detection dataclass. End-to-end verified: cello.vn Slick null -> 1.8.0 recovered. Generic across all Wappalyzer scriptSrc-firing techs, not Slick-specific.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:38.239Z","files":["D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/fp/wappalyzer.py","D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/fp/scanner.py"],"id":"mem_mp9oxxq8_e7e58ba0d8a5","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Wappalyzer evidence_url propagation (fixed 2026-05-17). Producer-side plumbing f","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:38.239Z","version":1},"mem_mp9oxylf_b95f0258a1f4":{"concepts":["SlugReadmeStage","wordpress-plugins","readme.txt","stable-tag","name-normalization","funnel-stage-6","slug_url_rules"],"content":"SlugReadmeStage (added 2026-05-17) -- generic uniform stage in the ┬¦7a detection funnel. Triggers when any detection's evidence_url matches a rule in lab_src_rules section='slug_url_rules'. Each rule encodes URL-shape that discloses (slug, version): URL regex captures slug, body regex captures version, tech name templated from slug. Generic by design -- WordPress plugins (/wp-content/plugins/<slug>/readme.txt -> Stable tag:) are first user, but Drupal modules / Composer vendors / etc. are just additional rule rows with no code change. Companion: pipeline._canonical_name_from_url normalizes nuclei \"X Detection\" template names back to plugin slug when URL is a WP plugin readme path -- so original nuclei detection (name='Polylang Detection', no version) and new readme detection (name='polylang', version=3.1.1) reconcile under one TechRecord key. Validated on centralretail.com.vn: 12/12 plugins recovered with proper slug names + Stable tag versions. Source-grounded: WordPress.org plugin readme.txt spec mandates Stable tag line.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:39.362Z","files":["D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/fp/stages.py","D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/fp/pipeline.py"],"id":"mem_mp9oxylf_b95f0258a1f4","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"SlugReadmeStage (added 2026-05-17) -- generic uniform stage in the ┬¦7a detection","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:39.362Z","version":1},"mem_mp9oxzke_c2a4c936c37e":{"concepts":["cdn-check","curl_cffi","ja3-fingerprint","false-positive","pre-flight","voz.vn"],"content":"cdn_check.check() fingerprint alignment (fixed 2026-05-17). The pre-flight CDN-block detector must use the SAME TLS fingerprint as the actual scanner, or it produces false positives that mark targets as \"blocked\" when the scanner itself sails through. Before: aiohttp (stdlib SSL fingerprint) -- voz.vn's Cloudflare bot management challenged it with 403+\"Just a moment\" interstitial. Scanner's curl_cffi(impersonate=chrome120) on same target got 200+full body. After: cdn_check.check() now uses curl_cffi+chrome120+fetchlib.build_request_headers() -- same fingerprint as scanner._fetch. False-positive eliminated, cdn_blocked field now means \"the scanner itself will be blocked\" as its docstring claims. Note: cfg.use_cloak short-circuits _should_escalate in pipeline.py so even genuine blocks don't trigger Stage 5 page-mode escalation when user already opted into cloak api mode -- worth knowing when diagnosing future \"escalation didn't fire\" reports.","createdAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:40.620Z","files":["D:/DATN2/fingerprinter/fp/cdn_check.py"],"id":"mem_mp9oxzke_c2a4c936c37e","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"cdn_check.check() fingerprint alignment (fixed 2026-05-17). The pre-flight CDN-b","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-05-17T11:27:40.620Z","version":1}}␀␀␀ēš␀␀┤╩  